    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of flowering tree native to southern Mexico and northern Central America. The leaves and bark are used in various medical applications. It was long a natural source of reddish and bluish dye, still an important source of haematoxylin used in histology for staining.</Note_Text>
